Section 1:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 964
H.P. 623 House of Representatives, March 11, 2025
Inland Fisheries and Wildlife Laws to Better Allow for Variations in
Timing Across the State
Received by the Clerk of the House on March 6, 2025. Referred to the Committee on
Inland Fisheries and Wildlife pursuant to Joint Rule 308.2 and ordered printed pursuant to Joint
Rule 401.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative SIMMONS of Waldoboro.
Printed on recycled paper
1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 12 MRSA §10001, sub-§60, as affected by PL 2003, c. 614, §9 and
3 amended by c. 655, Pt. B, §10 and affected by §422, is further amended to read:
4 60. Sunrise. "Sunrise" means, for a given location in the State, the time computed
5 and established for sunrise for Bangor, Maine, by the Nautical Almanac Office that location
6 by the Astronomical Applications Department of the United States Naval Observatory,
7 converted to the legal standard of time in force in this State on that day.
8 Sec. 2. 12 MRSA §10001, sub-§61, as affected by PL 2003, c. 614, §9 and
9 amended by c. 655, Pt. B, §10 and affected by §422, is further amended to read:
10 61. Sunset. "Sunset" means, for a given location in the State, the time computed and
11 established for sunset for Bangor, Maine, by the Nautical Almanac Office that location by
12 the Astronomical Applications Department of the United States Naval Observatory,
13 converted to the legal standard of time in force in this State on that day.
14 SUMMARY
1155 This bill amends the inland fisheries and wildlife law to change the entity within the
1166 United States Naval Observatory that the State relies upon to determine the times for
1177 sunrise and sunset from the Nautical Almanac Office to the Astronomical Applications
1188 Department and removes references to Bangor, Maine.
